14
00:02:15,910 --> 00:02:17,280
What exactly is the law?

15
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:20,310
Is it a code of conduct,

16
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:22,370
or a tool for people to use?

17
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:25,810
The law is people's

18
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,250
expectation for a better life.

19
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:34,280
The consensus of the expectations
is the law.

20
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,290
Law is a fiction created by people,

21
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,750
yet it constrains people
in their real life.

22
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:39,360
Yes.

23
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:41,840
For ordinary people,

24
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:44,110
it's invisible and intangible,

25
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:46,520
yet it's ubiquitous like the air.

26
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:48,710
People don't really understand

27
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:50,970
where the true boundaries of the law lie.

28
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:53,030
However, what constitutes a crime

29
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:54,430
and how it should be sentenced

30
00:02:54,430 --> 00:02:56,710
are all determined by these boundaries.

31
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,540
You still like asking questions,
don't you?

32
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:04,730
Force of habit.

33
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:08,560
Then, I'd like to ask you something too.

34
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,840
Who exactly

35
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:14,520
disclosed Jiang Ting's home address

36
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,910
to Zhang Yuan?

37
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,860
That has nothing to do with your case.

38
00:03:22,190 --> 00:03:25,030
I was once the lead prosecutor
of Jiang Ting's case.

39
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:26,470
Judicial accountability

40
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:27,470
lasts a lifetime.

41
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,750
I'm just detained,

42
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,079
not dead.

43
00:03:34,079 --> 00:03:34,750
True.

44
00:03:39,710 --> 00:03:41,970
The most suspicious person is Mei Zheng,

45
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:44,740
because only she knew
Jiang Ting's address.

46
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:46,520
However…

47
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,579
I think someone else might aslo be it.

48
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:54,680
Li Mufeng.

49
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,670
He didn't want Mei Zheng to be in danger.

50
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,190
He didn't want Mei Zheng

51
00:04:02,190 --> 00:04:03,630
to get involved in the dispute

52
00:04:03,630 --> 00:04:05,560
between Jiang Ting and Zhang Yuan.

53
00:04:06,630 --> 00:04:07,400
So, he secretly

54
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,430
gave Jiang Ting's home address

55
00:04:09,710 --> 00:04:11,110
to Zhang Yuan in advance.

56
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,760
While Mei Zheng was away,

57
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:15,570
Zhang Yuan forcibly entered
Jiang Ting's home.

58
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:16,560
This way,

59
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:18,310
